# CTEs, subqueries & SQL joins

## Three ways to compose queries

- **CTEs** тАФ `WITH ... AS (...)` names intermediate results тЖТ reads **top-to-bottom, not inside-out**
- **Subqueries** тАФ correlated & uncorrelated, in `WHERE` / `FROM` / `SELECT`
  - **scalar** (one value) ┬╖ **`IN`** (set membership) ┬╖ **`EXISTS`** (correlated)
- **Joins** тАФ all six, same semantics as the DataFrame `how`
  - `INNER` ┬╖ `LEFT` / `RIGHT` / `FULL OUTER` ┬╖ `LEFT SEMI` / `LEFT ANTI`

## Takeaway

- Everything from DataFrame joins & set logic applies тАФ **only the syntax differs**
